Dubov, Daniil (2723) - Grischuk, Alexander (2724)
World Rapid Team Championship (chess24.com) [7] 2023.08.27

1.d4 Nf6 2.Nf3 d5 3.c4 e6 4.g3 Be7 5.Bg2 O-O 6.O-O dxc4 7.Qc2 a6 8.a4 Bd7 9.Bg5 Bc6 10.Rd1 b5 11.Bxf6 Bxf6 12.Nc3 Qe8 13.d5 Bxd5 14.axb5 Bxc3 15.Ng5 g6 16.Qxc3 Qxb5 17.Nxf7 Kxf7 18.Ra5 Qb3 19.Qxb3 cxb3 20.Rdxd5 Ke7 21.Rd3 Ra7 22.Rxb3 Nd7 23.Bh3 Rb8 24.Rxb8 Nxb8 25.Re5 Rb7 26.Rxe6+ Kd8 27.Rf6 Rxb2 28.Rf7 Rxe2 29.Rxh7 a5 30.Rg7 a4 31.Bf1 Re8 32.Rxg6 Nd7 33.Bb5 Re4 34.Rg8+

00:00 Hello Everyone!
14:30 Richard Rapport vs Etienne Bacrot

The World Rapid Team Championship is a 12-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 August 2023 in Dusseldorf, Germany. Each team must field 6 players each round, including at least one woman and one "recreational" player who has never been rated above 2000.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. Teams receive 2 match points for a win, and 1 for a draw. Official website: worldrapidteams2023.fide.com
